messages.content: ComfyUI-Florence-2 is an extension or custom node for ComfyUI that integrates the Microsoft Florence-2-large model, supporting various output types.
Which models are supported by ComfyUI-Florence-2?
ComfyUI-Florence-2 supports all four models of the Microsoft Florence-2-large model.
What output types are initially supported by ComfyUI-Florence-2?
ComfyUI-Florence-2 provides initial support for all output types of the Microsoft Florence-2-large model.
What is the purpose of the example images provided for ComfyUI-Florence-2?
The example images demonstrate the capabilities and usage of ComfyUI-Florence-2, showcasing different output types such as workflow, bounding box, and segmentation.
What is on the TODO list for ComfyUI-Florence-2?
The TODO list for ComfyUI-Florence-2 includes implementing an all-in-one CLIP masked conditioning node.
Is ComfyUI-Florence-2 limited to specific output types?
No, ComfyUI-Florence-2 is designed to support all output types of the Microsoft Florence-2-large model.
Can ComfyUI-Florence-2 be used for image segmentation tasks?
Yes, based on the provided example image 'workflow_seg_crop.png', ComfyUI-Florence-2 can be used for image segmentation tasks.
